name: treatment of municipal solid waste, open burning | municipal solid waste | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/19144/documentation

This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'municipal solid waste' in uncontrolled, open burning. Recommended use of this dataset: This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of waste glass in uncontrolled, open burning.Inventoried waste contains 21% paper; 8% Mixed cardboard; 15% plastics; 3% laminated materials; 2% laminated packaging, e.g. tetra bricks; 3% combined goods e.g.  diapers; 3% glass; 2% textiles; 8% minerals; 9% natural products; 22% compostable material; 2.65% inert metals; 1% volatile metals; 0.0065% batteries; 0.34% electronic goods;. Waste composition (wet, in ppm): upper heating value 13.27 MJ/kg; lower heating value 11.74 MJ/kg; H2O 228830; O 257060; H 48250; C 334230; S 1119; N 3123.8; P 893.79; B 7.1933; Cl 6866.2; Br 13.552; F 56.358; I 0.0121; Ag 0.714; As 0.62521; Ba 149.04; Cd 11.748; Co 1.3453; Cr 315.21; Cu 1212.8; Hg 1.4424; Mn 259.36; Mo 1.9551; Ni 107.38; Pb 502.43; Sb 22.564; Se 0.31969; Sn 73.44; V 9.2147; Zn 1311.2; Be n.a.; Sc n.a.; Sr n.a.; Ti n.a.; Tl n.a.; W n.a.; Si 48510; Fe 29996; Ca 14062; Al 12420; K 2059.7; Mg 3377.7; Na 5143.9; . Share of carbon in waste that is biogenic 60.4%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) iron: 60%, aluminium: 17.8%, copper: 72.8%, .Recycling rates for metallic iron = 95% for metallic aluminium = 0% for metallic copper = 95% . From the burn residues 0.0171kg iron, 0.000839kg copper, are separated and recycled. A mass of 0.21kg residues are left on ground. 

The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the uncontrolled disposal location is not included.


The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open burning are released to the environment (air and soil).
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/382:Waste treatment and disposal/3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste

processDocumentation.timeDescription: This dataset represents a generic open burning without any temporal distinction.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Modelling parameters representing a generic open burning process, not geographical specific.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This is an inventory for open burning of solid waste. Informal or uncontrolled burning. No flue gas treatment. Suitable for informal recycling (e.g. burning of e-waste). Based on Municipal waste incineration without any pollution control. Residues (minus any actually recycled metals) are left on site. Assumption of share of thermal NOx to total NOx in average waste burning process is 30%. Contribution from thermal NOx is 810mg per kg waste. Recycling rates for metallic iron = 95% for metallic aluminium = 0% for metallic copper = 95% .
